        "response": "**Title: \"Stand Up, Speak Out\"**\n\n**INT. SCHOOL HALLWAY - DAY**\n\n*The camera pans across a busy school hallway. Students are chatting, laughing, and heading to their classes. The camera focuses on a group of students whispering and pointing at another student, JAMES, who is walking alone, looking downcast.*\n\n**NARRATOR (V.O.)**\n(soft, concerned tone)\nEvery day, countless students face the harsh reality of bullying.\n\n*James walks past the group, trying to ignore the whispers. The camera zooms in on his face, showing his sadness and isolation.*\n\n**CUT TO: INT. CLASSROOM - DAY**\n\n*James sits at his desk, trying to focus on his work. The whispers and giggles from the group of students continue in the background.*\n\n**NARRATOR (V.O.)**\nBut it doesn't have to be this way.\n\n*The camera shifts to another student, EMMA, who notices James's distress. She looks thoughtful for a moment, then stands up and walks over to James.*\n\n**EMMA**\nHey, James. Do you want to sit with us at lunch today?\n\n*James looks up, surprised and grateful. He nods slowly.*\n\n**JAMES**\nYeah, I'd like that. Thanks, Emma.\n\n**CUT TO: INT. SCHOOL CAFETERIA - DAY**\n\n*James sits with Emma and her friends. They are laughing and talking, and James is smiling for the first time. The camera captures the warmth and camaraderie at the table.*\n\n**NARRATOR (V.O.)**\nA small act of kindness can make a world of difference.\n\n**CUT TO: INT. SCHOOL HALLWAY - DAY**\n\n*The camera shows Emma and her friends standing up to the group of bullies, calmly but firmly telling them to stop their behavior. The bullies look taken aback and walk away.*\n\n**NARRATOR (V.O.)**\nStanding up against bullying takes courage, but together, we can create a safe and supportive environment for everyone.\n\n**CUT TO: INT. SCHOOL ASSEMBLY HALL - DAY**\n\n*The entire school is gathered for an assembly. A TEACHER stands at the podium, addressing the students.*\n\n**TEACHER**\nWe all have a role to play in stopping bullying. Let's make our school a place where everyone feels valued and respected.\n\n**CUT TO: INT. SCHOOL HALLWAY - DAY**\n\n*The camera shows students being kind to each other, helping one another, and standing up against bullying. James is now walking confidently, surrounded by friends.*\n\n**NARRATOR (V.O.)**\nStand up. Speak out. Together, we can end bullying.\n\n**TEXT ON SCREEN:**\n\"End Bullying Now. Stand Up, Speak Out.\"\n\n**FADE OUT.**\n\n**END.**"
